This paper discusses the practical implementation of Linked Data and its application to mathematical functionality. Therefore, it is likely to fall under the categories of Artificial Intelligence (cs.AI) and Databases (cs.DB) as these fields are concerned with the organization and retrieval of data. Additionally, the paper discusses the Linking Open Data movement, which falls under the category of Logic in Computer Science (cs.LO). The paper also discusses real-world scenarios, which may fall under the category of Software Engineering (cs.SE) and Programming Languages (cs.PL).
